The course concentrates on the standards of orthography, morphology, syntax and lexicology of the contemporary written Estonian. The different types of texts, various styles and the peculiarities of written and oral expression are treated.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To teach the students how to produce and understand texts in various situations, also how to see the importance and the role of the language in their activities. Special attention is given to the linguistic and textual features of journalism and PR.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student is able to compile a well-written and correct text; correct his or her mistakes, if necessary; see the differences between different sublanguages and  functional styles; use the main sources of practical language planning (dictionaries, handbooks, websites, databases etc).
